body.description: Our most earth conscious diapers yet feature a wetness indicator, better absorption & blowout protection, cloud-like comfort and unique features for each babe stage – all while using less material and helping save over 7000 trees every single year. Plus, a secure, comfy fit for less sag + more swag. What Makes A Clean Conscious Diaper? To make the core of the diaper, we harvest wood from sustainably managed pine + spruce trees in Scandinavia, which is then turned into fluff pulp at a Swedish mill using totally chlorine-free processing. We don't add latex, fragrance, or parabens. We use a 100% plant-based backsheet, and our new, more efficient design reduces the amount of material used in each diaper. Our diapers are cruelty-free and never tested on animals. Our diaper boxes are made from 100% PCR post recycled consumer cardboard (aka they’re 100% recyclable) – that means no new trees cut down and no landfill, if recycled.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars BEST diapers on the market!
reviews.reviewText: These are absolutely the best diapers for your baby! You will not be disappointed. (No one paid me to say that!) I read lots of reviews as a new mom and tried lots of diapers. These are not only one of the few diapers that doesn’t cause rashes on my baby’s skin, but they also have never once leaked in the 5 months we’ve been using them, there are never faulty diaper tabs like other brands, and they are very cute! The diaper rash he had in the NOCU immediately went away when we switched to these diapers. When I ran out of Honest and went back to pampers for a week, the rash came back but again went away right away with Honest diapers. Honest also has the best wipes fyi!!! Take my word from a mom who reads every review and tries everything so you don’t have to!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are the best
reviews.reviewText: Quality- the fit perfect and absorb better than the competitors. The “popular” brand we were using not only caused a rash but wouldn’t last through the night. These have been the only brand his skin can handle. Him and I get ALOT more sleep now that I don’t have to wake up in the middle of the night to change him.Appearance- There are so many patterns that it’s hard to pick which one I’ll put on him (this is the only down side lol). All the doctors and nurses that have seen us change him during a visit are so stoked about the designs that they ask the brand and where they can get them - whether for their own baby, or to gift. Right now my favorite is the skulls. They are cute and cool.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 13/10 Would Poop Here Again
reviews.reviewText: Maybe it's the way our baby is shaped but we had many leaks with Pampers Swaddlers once our little guy started really soaking diapers. We'd been given a couple packs of newborn Honest diapers as hand-me-downs so we gave it a shot and now it's all our baby wears. Sure we still have the occasional blowout (who doesn't?) but the only urine leaks have been due to human error (remember to make sure the penis is INSIDE the diaper). Honestly, the blowouts have only happened to my partner so maybe those were human error too, haha. These diapers are great. They're absorbent, they trap those liquidy breastmilk poops well, and they're super cute. I wish they cost a little less but if you stock up during sales they're not too bad.
